<item>
            <title>[LU-18735] sanity/test_413a and conf-sanity/test_32[b,c,e,h] permanent timeout/failures with ZFS back-end only</title>
                <link>https://jira.whamcloud.com/browse/LU-18735</link>
                <project id="10000" key="LU">Lustre</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;sanity/test_413a failure/timeout example at &lt;a href=&quot;https://testing.whamcloud.com/test_sets/2398dece-98fe-44d8-b89d-3c76dbef0216&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;https://testing.whamcloud.com/test_sets/2398dece-98fe-44d8-b89d-3c76dbef0216&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;conf-sanity/test_32&lt;span class=&quot;error&quot;&gt;&amp;#91;b,c,e,h&amp;#93;&lt;/span&gt; failures example at &lt;a href=&quot;https://testing.whamcloud.com/test_sets/431e1d95-39e3-43bb-b721-df2e51d0ea6f&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;https://testing.whamcloud.com/test_sets/431e1d95-39e3-43bb-b721-df2e51d0ea6f&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;all look directly related to &lt;a href=&quot;https://jira.whamcloud.com/browse/LU-18646&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow&quot;&gt;LU-18646&lt;/a&gt; findings (&quot;&lt;em&gt;&lt;b&gt;dd if=/dev/zero ...&lt;/b&gt;&lt;/em&gt;&quot; commands do not consume expected space due to ZFS recently using data compression by default) and could be fixed the same way (&lt;a href=&quot;https://review.whamcloud.com/c/fs/lustre-release/+/57871&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;https://review.whamcloud.com/c/fs/lustre-release/+/57871&lt;/a&gt;).&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;there are more conf-sanity subtests failures following but they do not look directly caused by this same problem and may only be consequences of the first failures...&lt;/p&gt;</description>
